data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime — no opt-in can save them.**

EF Core 11 **fully removed** sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider. In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but that escape hatch is gone. Every method in your repository that calls a synchronous API (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) will throw unconditionally.

**Fix:** Convert to async throughout:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to update all callers to `await` these methods and propagate `async` up the call chain. There is no workaround — the Cosmos DB SDK is async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.

Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059)
